.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:7:  - "advisor weight calibration"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:14:Process, measurement methodology, decision framework, approval gates plus rollback criteria for changing scorer lane weights in mk_skill_advisor.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:22:Defines the evidence, measurement and rollback workflow for changing live advisor scorer lane weights.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:36:- [`advisor_scorer.md`](./advisor_scorer.md)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:46:- A baseline `advisor_validate` run shows top-1 accuracy below 80.5% on the full corpus or below 77.5% on the holdout set.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:54:- "It feels low for lane X." Without measured evidence, intuition mispredicts the cross-skill impact.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:55:- "We just added this skill." Single-skill tuning belongs in the explicit_author lane's curated boosts (`mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts`), not in global lane weights.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/lane_weight_tuning.md:56:- "The semantic lane scored higher than expected." The semantic_shadow lane carries `shadowOnly=true` so it does not affect live ranking. Adjust the shadow_weight if you want to tune shadow mode, not the live weight.
