.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:19:Validate that `lib/derived/anti-stuffing.ts` enforces cardinality caps on derived entries, demotes tokens with suspicious repetition density and rejects adversarial fixtures designed to stuff the routing surface.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:27:- Pre-built adversarial fixtures under `scripts/fixtures/` or equivalent. Otherwise generate a SKILL.md with >500 repeated trigger phrases as an isolated fixture.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:33:> **Structure deviation note (007-deferred-final).** This scenario uses a numbered-step plus Expected Signals plus Failure Modes shape instead of the canonical Prompt/Commands/Expected/Evidence/Pass-Fail/Failure-Triage subsections. The deviation is intentional for this skill playbook category to keep scenario semantics tightly bound to runtime output checks. See `references/decisions/deferred_decisions.md` §F34 for rationale.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:35:1. Copy an existing active skill into the disposable copy and duplicate a trigger phrase 1000 times in its body.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:36:2. Add a second fixture where a single n-gram is repeated with only punctuation variation.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:40:touch /tmp/path-to-copy/.opencode/skills/adversarial-fixture/SKILL.md
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:43:4. Read the fixture's `graph-metadata.json.derived` block.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:44:5. Call `advisor_recommend` with a prompt that would match the stuffed n-gram. Compare the fixture's derived lane score against a normal skill.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:48:- The fixture's derived entries respect a hard cardinality cap (not every repetition is stored).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:49:- Tokens with high repetition density receive demoted weights relative to normal skills.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:50:- Known adversarial fixtures (per the bundled test suite) are rejected and excluded from routing.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/06--auto-indexing/005-anti-stuffing.md:51:- The fixture does not outrank an honest candidate in `advisor_recommend` output.
