.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:3:> First release-cleanup pass on the deep-loop-runtime skill. Documentation-only changes. No code, scripts, tests or storage touched.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:9:The deep-loop-runtime v1.0.0 baseline shipped the arc-118 FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation but the documentation surface had never been audited end to end against the current sk-doc templates or HVR voice standards. The README was undersized at 174 LOC with only 6 of the 9 sections that the system-spec-kit README structural anchor prescribes. The SKILL.md frontmatter description was 240 chars (over the 130-char skill limit). Two artifacts (SKILL.md and README.md) carried a broken changelog path reference (`v1.0.0.md` instead of `v1.0.0.0.md`). A top-level `## Council Primitives` H2 inside section 3 broke the numbered-H2-ALL-CAPS rule.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:25:- 3.3 Scoring and routing (2 modules: bayesian-scorer, fallback-router)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:31:Every domain row identifies the consuming skill (`deep-review`, `deep-research`, `deep-ai-council`) so cross-system connections are explicit.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:53:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md` | Full rewrite. 174 LOC -> 470 LOC. New sections: OVERVIEW (How It Compares, Requirements), CONFIGURATION, USAGE EXAMPLES, TROUBLESHOOTING, FAQ. Existing sections expanded to cover all 7 runtime domains plus council primitives plus storage. |
