.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/helpers/README.md:3:description: "Shared test-fixture utilities reused across deep-loop-runtime test suites."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/helpers/README.md:12:vitest fixture helpers reused across multiple test files. Renamed from `_helpers` to honor the no-underscore folder convention.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/helpers/README.md:20:## 3. RELATED RESOURCES
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/helpers/README.md:22:- Parent tests README: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/README.md`
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:1:This is the first shipped release of `deep-loop-runtime`. The earlier `v0.1.0` state was a phase-001 scaffold. Version `1.0.0` marks the runtime as populated and verified: shared deep-loop libraries, coverage-graph ownership, direct script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests now live together in the peer skill instead of inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:3:> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/003-deep-loop-runtime/009-verification-changelog-closeout/` (Level 2)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:9:Before 118, every change to the deep-review or deep-research loop infrastructure required touching files inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`. Two consumer skills (`deep-review`, `deep-research`) depended on internals of a third skill (`system-spec-kit`), and the MCP tool surface (`mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*`) added a marshalling layer between workflow YAMLs and the SQLite-backed coverage graph. The arrangement was accumulated drift from early MCP server scaffolding; no ADR justified it. Arc 118 (FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP, user-directive override of the 117 AI Council SPLIT ruling) consolidated all deep-loop runtime infrastructure into this peer skill, removed the MCP tool surface entirely, and replaced it with direct `.cjs` script invocation — the same pattern `reduce-state.cjs` already used. Workflow YAML calls became one-step (`bash: node .../scripts/<name>.cjs`) instead of two-step (MCP-dispatch then JSON-parse).
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:19:- **Deep-loop support code** — Ten shared TypeScript modules now live under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/`: executor config, executor audit, prompt-pack rendering, post-dispatch validation, atomic state, JSONL repair, loop locking, permissions, Bayesian scoring, and fallback routing. Each carries a `MODULE:` header per the OpenCode TypeScript style guide.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:23:- **Graph schema and queries** — Three coverage-graph modules live under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/`: `coverage-graph-db.ts` (SQLite schema + connection lifecycle + node-kind allow-list), `coverage-graph-query.ts` (query builders), and `coverage-graph-signals.ts` (convergence signal extraction). The runtime-owned SQLite database is at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/storage/deep-loop-graph.sqlite`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:32:- Each script parses CLI args (`--spec-folder`, `--loop-type`, `--session-id`, etc.), opens the SQLite DB in a try block, calls the relevant lib function, writes JSON to stdout, and closes the DB in a finally block.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:38:- **Split by responsibility** — Runtime-focused unit, integration, and lifecycle tests moved into `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/`:
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:40:  - `tests/integration/` (4 script-spawn tests + 3 Phase B review-depth fixtures)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:51:- **graph-metadata.json** — peer-skill discoverability metadata (trigger phrases, key topics, entities, dependencies, related_to)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:57:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md` | Version bumped from `0.1.0` to `1.0.0`; scaffold wording replaced with shipped-layout details, SMART ROUTING + HOW IT WORKS + RULES sections added per sk-doc canonical template. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:58:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md` | Authored with YAML frontmatter, TOC, OVERVIEW, QUICK START, FEATURES, STRUCTURE, INTEGRATION POINTS, RELATED DOCUMENTS sections per sk-doc README template. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:59:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` | 10 shared runtime modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:60:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/` | 3 coverage-graph modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:61:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/{convergence,upsert,query,status}.cjs` | Direct entry points replacing the 4 removed `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:62:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs` | Shared input-validation + exit-code-classification helpers extracted during the post-review fix-pack. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:63:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/storage/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` | Runtime-owned SQLite database. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:64:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/{unit,integration,lifecycle,_helpers}/` | Runtime-owned Vitest coverage for libraries, scripts, and DB lifecycle. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:65:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/` | 18-file canonical catalog. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:66:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/` | 18-file canonical playbook. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:67:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/` | 4 canonical reference docs. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:68:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json` | Peer-skill discoverability metadata. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:72:Consumers should call the four `.cjs` scripts directly rather than attempting to use the deleted `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools. The migration source was `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`; after arc 118, the runtime owner is `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`. Workflow YAMLs (`spec_kit_deep-{review,research}_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) were updated to invoke the scripts via `bash:` blocks; `/doctor` diagnostics and the `system-code-graph` playbook scenario 009 were updated correspondingly. The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob was extended to discover tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:83:bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder "{spec_folder}" --loop-type "review" --session-id "{session_id}"'
