.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:18:`lib/scorer/` contains the native scoring modules used by the skill advisor to rank candidate skills. It combines lane-specific evidence, text matching, age policy, ambiguity handling, explicit alias canonicalization, fusion and output projection into prompt-safe recommendation scores.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:24:- Canonicalizes narrow command/skill alias groups before campaign scoring compares expected and actual routes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:25:- Supports attribution and ablation helpers for advisor quality checks.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:35:+-- aliases.ts               # Narrow command/skill alias canonicalization
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:55:| `fusion.ts` | Combines lane scores into final advisor ranking signals. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:57:| `aliases.ts` | Canonicalizes explicit command/skill alias groups for route comparisons. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:59:| `ambiguity.ts` | Detects close or unclear recommendation states. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:71:| Exports | Export scorer functions and types, not handler response formatting. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:73:| Aliases | Keep command/skill aliases fixed and explicit. Do not use fuzzy or prefix matching. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/README.md:78:prompt and candidate skills
