.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:3:description: "Test fixtures for council graph value scenarios, providing scenario fixtures and shared helper utilities that compare runtime CLI graph performance against baseline file reads."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:5:  - "council value fixtures"
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:13:> Layered fixture directory that provides scenario fixtures and shared seeding utilities for validating runtime council graph query performance against baseline file reading operations.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:19:`tests/fixtures/council-value/` owns scenario fixtures and helper utilities for the council graph value demonstration system. Each scenario measures the performance improvement of runtime CLI council graph queries over baseline file reading approaches. The fixtures cover six council graph query types: unresolved disagreements, decision support, convergence, convergence blockers, hot nodes and status queries.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:23:- 7 TypeScript files and a `data/` subdirectory provide the full fixture surface.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:24:- Six scenario fixture files (`dac-027.ts` through `dac-032.ts`) each export a fixture constant implementing the `ScenarioFixture` interface.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:26:- Each scenario fixture loads test data from `data/scenarios.cjs`, which defines graph seeds (nodes and edges), artifact trees and expected answers.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:27:- Fixtures call `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/{upsert,query,status,convergence}.cjs --loop-type council` through the shared script helper, with direct DB reads only for fixture-side ranking normalization.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:28:- The consumer test `tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.vitest.ts` compares `graph.runtimeCalls` against `baseline.fileReads` and writes its performance metrics report to a temp path by default. Set `COUNCIL_VALUE_REPORT_PATH=.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/council-graph-value-report.json` only when intentionally refreshing the tracked report.
