.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:51:│  │  │ derived  │ │validate  │ │                          │   │  │
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:52:│  │  │ semantic │ │          │ │                          │   │  │
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:59:│  │ skill_advisor  │────▶│ skill-graph     │                     │
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:84:│   ├── lib/                # Skill graph, trust state, helpers
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:85:│   ├── database/           # Local SQLite skill graph
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:109:The advisor treats its SQLite skill graph as the durable record. Recommendations are read-only over that record; the daemon refreshes it from authored skill metadata.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:111:**Read path (`advisor_recommend`):** input prompt enters `handlers/recommend.ts`, the scorer fuses 5 lanes, the result joins with trust-state metadata, and the handler returns a calibrated `recommendations[]` array with prompt-safe attribution.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:113:**Write path (`advisor_rebuild`):** the rebuilder scans `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` and `graph-metadata.json`, applies the affordance normalizer, persists rows to the skill graph, and bumps the generation counter. Daemon watches the same paths and triggers incremental rebuilds on file change.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:118:- `mcp_server/lib/skill-graph/rebuild.ts` owns the write path.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:125:The MCP server is composed of focused subsystems that share the transport layer and the SQLite skill graph.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:127:**Scorer.** Five lanes fuse into a single calibrated score: explicit author signals, lexical overlap, skill-graph causality, derived metadata, and a semantic shadow lane. The fusion respects per-lane weights and emits per-lane attribution alongside the final score. Tool detail and lane semantics live in `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:129:**Daemon and freshness.** A chokidar watcher under `daemon/` observes `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` and per-skill `graph-metadata.json` files. On change, it triggers an incremental rebuild and refreshes the trust-state vocabulary: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, `unavailable`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:131:**Skill graph.** A SQLite database holds the cross-skill edges (depends_on, dependents, enhances, conflicts) plus per-skill metadata. The `skill_graph_query` tool exposes read-only graph traversal.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:133:**Compatibility shim.** `compat/skill_advisor.py` keeps scripts and hooks working when the native MCP path is not reachable. The shim wraps the same recommendation logic with a Python entrypoint.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:147:**Release validation.** `advisor_validate` runs the regression suite and reports threshold semantics (aggregate vs runtime) plus a prompt-safe `telemetry.outcomes.totals` block. Hook diagnostics persist to bounded JSONL sinks so `advisor_validate` can read them back across processes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:157:| ADR-001 | Five-lane scorer with explicit weights and prompt-safe attribution | Accepted |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md:158:| ADR-002 | Daemon-backed freshness via chokidar watching SKILL.md + graph-metadata.json | Accepted |
