.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:2:title: "Python CLI Shim (skill_advisor.py)"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:6:  - "skill_advisor.py"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:11:# Python CLI Shim (skill_advisor.py)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:17:Keep pre-Phase-027 Python consumers working while moving routing to the native advisor. The shim probes the native daemon first, translates native output into the legacy JSON-array shape and falls back to the local Python scorer when native routing is unavailable or explicitly bypassed.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:21:`scripts/skill_advisor.py` is the CLI surface. `scripts/skill_advisor_runtime.py` implements the local Python scorer used by `--force-local` and the fallback path. Control flags:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:28:| `--threshold <value>` | Override dual-threshold confidence cutoff (default 0.8). |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:38:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py` | Script | Source reference |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/01-cli-shim.md:39:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_runtime.py` | Script | Source reference |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/05-advisor-rebuild.md:3:description: "Explicit operator MCP tool that rebuilds the native advisor skill graph from checked-in skill metadata when advisor_status reports stale, absent or unavailable state."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/05-advisor-rebuild.md:8:  - "skill graph rebuild"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/05-advisor-rebuild.md:17:Give operators an explicit repair path for stale, absent or unavailable advisor state without hiding rebuild side effects inside `advisor_status`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/05-advisor-rebuild.md:21:`advisor_rebuild` is the explicit MCP repair tool that keeps rebuild behavior out of `advisor_status`. The handler reads the current status first. If status is `live` and `force` is not true, it skips the rebuild and returns a diagnostic telling the caller to pass `force:true` when a live rebuild is intentional.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/05-advisor-rebuild.md:23:When rebuild proceeds, it indexes `.opencode/skills/`, publishes a fresh skill-graph generation with `reason: "advisor_rebuild"`, rereads status and returns freshness before/after, generation before/after, skill count, indexing summary and warnings. `advisor_status` remains diagnostic-only and never repairs stale state.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/05-advisor-rebuild.md:25:The tool descriptor and dispatcher register `advisor_rebuild` alongside `advisor_recommend`, `advisor_status` and `advisor_validate`. The standalone advisor server currently exposes eight public tools: four `advisor_*` tools and four `skill_graph_*` tools.
