.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/03-bench-runner.md:2:title: "Python Bench Runner (skill_advisor_bench.py)"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/03-bench-runner.md:6:  - "skill_advisor_bench.py"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/03-bench-runner.md:11:# Python Bench Runner (skill_advisor_bench.py)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/03-bench-runner.md:21:`scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py` drives the bench measurements. The design envelope is `cache-hit p95 <= 50 ms` and `uncached p95 <= 60 ms`, design ceilings rather than enforceable CI gates, since p95 timing varies with sandbox load. Current stable-workstation measurements are 6.989 ms (cache-hit p95) and 11.45 ms (uncached p95), well within the envelope. Daemon-side idle measurements are 0.031% CPU and 5.516 MB RSS. The CI wrapper at `mcp_server/stress_test/skill-advisor/python-bench-runner-stress.vitest.ts` verifies the subprocess surface and JSON envelope shape. Tightened p95 gating belongs in a stable benchmark environment, not the stress suite.
