.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:44:The advisor reports one of four trust states in every response that touches the skill graph:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:48:| `live` | The index is fresh. Source SKILL.md plus graph-metadata.json files have not changed since the last build. The recommendation reflects current skill state. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:89:- `live → stale`: daemon detects a hash mismatch on any `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` or `graph-metadata.json` file.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:105:| MCP client (direct call) | Use recommendation directly | Call `advisor_rebuild` first if confidence matters | Call `advisor_rebuild`. Do not act on empty result | Wait for subsystem recovery or use Python shim |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:106:| Python shim (`skill_advisor.py`) | Use native response | Pass through with stale annotation | Compute fallback locally | Compute fallback locally |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:107:| Validation harness (`advisor_validate`) | Run as configured | Trigger rebuild before measurement | Trigger rebuild before measurement | Fail the validate run with clear error |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:113:- Treat `absent` as "no skill matches" and route to default. Always call `advisor_rebuild`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:122:- Watching `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` plus `.opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json` for mtime changes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:132:- Validating skill content. Only `skill_graph_validate` checks edge integrity.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:141:| Daemon dies | `advisor_status.daemon = "down"`, trustState may stay `live` until next file change but freshness detection lags | Restart the MCP server (`mk_skill_advisor` restarts the daemon on boot) |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:143:| SQLite corruption | `advisor_status.trustState = "absent"` even after rebuild attempts | Delete `mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite{,-wal,-shm}`, run `advisor_rebuild --force` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:144:| File watcher overflow (too many files) | Daemon stops detecting changes | Restart MCP server. Long-term: prune `.opencode/skills/` excludes |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/freshness_contract.md:153:- [`advisor_scorer.md`](../scoring/advisor_scorer.md), confidence calibration depends on trust state for some routes.
