.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/fixtures/README.md:9:# Skill Advisor Test Fixtures
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/02-lease.md:17:Prevent duplicate daemon writers from corrupting the advisor graph by ensuring exactly one daemon holds the workspace lease, with automatic reclaim when the prior owner dies.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/02-lease.md:21:`lib/daemon/lease.ts` acquires a SQLite-backed lease keyed by workspace root. A heartbeat row is refreshed at a fixed interval. If the heartbeat ages past the reclaim threshold, a new daemon can acquire the lease. Readers never block on the lease, `advisor_status` and `advisor_recommend` continue to serve cached or source-driven results even when no writer is active. The lease cooperates with `lib/freshness/trust-state.ts` to expose `absent` or `unavailable` trust state when there is no live writer.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/01--daemon-and-freshness/02-lease.md:49:- [05-trust-state.md](./05-trust-state.md), reader-visible trust semantics.
