.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:2:title: "Skill Advisor Cross-Skill Edges"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:3:description: "Report and optional apply helpers for inferred inbound enhances edges across skill graph metadata."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:10:# Skill Advisor Cross-Skill Edges
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:18:`lib/cross-skill-edges/` detects missing inbound `enhances` edges from skill metadata and can apply selected high-confidence candidates back to `graph-metadata.json`. Report mode is the default; write mode must stay explicit.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:26:| Candidate detection | Skill advisor | Uses metadata signals to infer inbound edge candidates. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:28:| Edge schema | System graph contracts | Keep public `skill_graph_*` tool IDs stable. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:39:| `apply-graph-metadata-patch.ts` | Applies selected candidates with path-boundary checks. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:48:- Keep apply mode explicit, scoped and path-boundary checked.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:49:- Do not rename public advisor or `skill_graph_*` MCP tool IDs from this folder.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/cross-skill-edges/README.md:77:- [`../skill-graph/README.md`](../skill-graph/README.md)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:2:title: "Skill Advisor Library: Runtime, Scoring And Metadata Helpers"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:10:# Skill Advisor Library: Runtime, Scoring And Metadata Helpers
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:18:`skill_advisor/lib/` owns the TypeScript helper layer behind advisor recommendation, prompt-safe rendering, daemon freshness checks, lifecycle metadata, compatibility probes and scorer behavior. Handlers and scripts call these modules instead of duplicating advisor logic.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:23:- Groups compatibility, daemon, derived metadata, freshness, lifecycle, scorer, shadow and utility modules in focused subfolders.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:65:+-- derived/                    # Derived metadata helpers
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:69:+-- lifecycle/                  # Skill lifecycle metadata helpers
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/README.md:137:| `cross-skill-edges/` | Detects and optionally applies inbound `enhances` graph edges. |
