.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:41:The `lib/skill-graph/` library resides inside the advisor skill package:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:44:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/skill-graph/
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:50:- `skill-graph-db.ts` - SQLite schema initialization and indexer writes
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:51:- `skill-graph-queries.ts` - Prepared relationship queries
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:53:The library owns the SQLite schema, indexing logic and relationship query helpers used by the `skill_graph_*` MCP tools.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:59:Before the realignment, [SKILL.md](../../SKILL.md) stated that `lib/skill-graph/` database and query logic remained in `system-spec-kit` until a pending cleanup. That historical claim sat near the bottom of SKILL.md before the realignment delta corrected it.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:61:That statement is outdated. The extraction completed earlier and no `skill-graph` folder exists under `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/`. File search across the spec-kit tree confirms the absence. The pending-cleanup reference is obsolete and was removed during the verified documentation delta. The current [SKILL.md §4 RULES](../../SKILL.md) plus §7 INTEGRATION POINTS reflect the post-extraction state.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:67:Extraction is complete. `lib/skill-graph/` is fully migrated to `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/skill-graph/`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:77:- Update [SKILL.md](../../SKILL.md) to state that extraction is complete. **Done**: ARCHITECTURE.md §1 plus §9 plus SKILL.md §4 RULES now describe `lib/skill-graph/` as package-local to system-skill-advisor.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_extraction_plan.md:81:No further refactor is planned for `lib/skill-graph/` itself. Future ownership changes would be tracked as a separate packet with its own ADR and migration plan.
