.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:305:**Worked example**: A healthy skill graph has zero orphans. Every skill should declare at least one outbound or inbound edge so the advisor can route to it via graph signals.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:307:**Gotcha**: An orphan skill will still surface in `advisor_recommend` if its explicit_author or lexical lanes score high enough. But the graph_causal lane contribution will be zero. Orphans are a signal to add at least one edge in the skill graph-metadata.json.
