.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:96:- `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status`, `skill_graph_validate`, unchanged.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.2.0.md:106:- **Embeddings dependency on system-spec-kit is intentional**, by user choice, the symlink at `lib/shared/embeddings` makes this visible rather than hidden. Embeddings-backed features (`semantic-shadow` scoring lane + `skill-graph-db` embedding load) require system-spec-kit/shared/embeddings to be present. The dangling symlink is the failure signal.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:2:title: "Skill Graph Propagate Enhances Tool"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:10:# Skill Graph Propagate Enhances Tool
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:20:Documents the internal `skill_graph_propagate_enhances` tool for detecting and optionally applying missing inbound `enhances` edges.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:24:- Auditing trusted-caller graph maintenance behavior.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:30:Enhance-edge propagation is a high-trust authoring helper: report first, write only with explicit trusted-caller intent.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:34:- `mcp_server/handlers/skill-graph/propagate-enhances.ts`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:41:Three rules contribute to the composite confidence score with capped maximum contributions:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:59:- `apply` - Writes selected candidates to source `graph-metadata.json` files.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:61:`apply` mode only writes candidates that are explicitly selected by ID or selected through `applyAllHighConfidence=true` for candidates above `minConfidence` (default 0.75). `dryRun` defaults to true so a fresh `apply` call without explicit `dryRun:false` still produces a no-write preview.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:71:- The default mode is `report`. No writes occur unless `mode:'apply'` is set explicitly.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:72:- The default `dryRun` is true. Writes only occur when `dryRun:false` is set explicitly.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:73:- `apply` mode only writes candidates that match an explicit `applyCandidateIds[]` entry OR meet `minConfidence` when `applyAllHighConfidence=true`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:87:The tool sits beside the eight other skill-graph tools as a low-frequency, high-trust authoring helper.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/legacy/advisor-fixtures/noPassingSkill.json:8:      "confidence": 0.61,
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/07--hooks-and-plugin/04-codex-hook.md:21:`hooks/codex/session-start.ts` handles native `SessionStart` startup, resume and clear events and returns `hookSpecificOutput.additionalContext`. `hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.ts` handles native `UserPromptSubmit` advisor briefs. User-level `~/.codex/hooks.json` registers the compiled `SessionStart` and `UserPromptSubmit` entries alongside Superset `notify.sh` and `~/.codex/config.toml` must enable `codex_hooks = true`. `hooks/codex/prompt-wrapper.ts` remains the fallback prompt-wrapper path for Codex deployments that do not expose the hook surface. `.codex/policy.json` ships the Bash denylist. The native prompt hook and wrapper share failure semantics and the global disable flag.
