.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:11:The advisor's metrics persistence in `mcp_server/lib/metrics.ts` used synchronous `mkdirSync` plus `writeFileSync` to flush diagnostic and outcome records, which blocked the event loop on every advisor invocation. The hot path is now `await mkdir` plus `await writeFile` from `fs/promises`, gated by a closure-scoped `dirReady = false` flag that ensures the directory check runs exactly once per process. The two persistence entrypoints (`persistAdvisorHookDiagnosticRecord` and `persistAdvisorHookOutcomeRecord`) are now async functions that await the underlying writes. Bounded-retention semantics, read the file, slice the last N records, rewrite the file, are preserved per the council's section 10.1 mandate, because making the writes fire-and-forget would have allowed unbounded growth between rotations.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:17:Advisor diagnostics used to flush on every invocation, even when no one was reading them. The new `SKILL_ADVISOR_DEBUG=1` enable gate keeps the persistence hot path quiet by default and only writes diagnostic records when an operator has explicitly opted in. Outcome records remain unconditional because they are part of the bounded-retention metrics contract.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:35:Both packets ran through a 5-seat deep-ai-council deliberation before any source change. The council returned REQUEST-CHANGES on the first pass with HIGH confidence and reshaped scope on three load-bearing points. First, the `metrics.ts` writes had to remain awaited so the bounded-retention read-then-rewrite-last-N pattern survives. Second, the plugin factory had to await the config promise before normalizing options. Third, the existing env-var disable handling at lines 35 through 39 had to be preserved unchanged so the disable surface remained stable. Implementation followed via `cli-opencode + deepseek-v4-pro --pure`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:53:| `.opencode/plugins/README.md` | Documents the new 4-tier precedence, the 7 `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_*` env-var fallbacks, the JSON config file path and the backward-compat note on `SPEC_KIT_PLUGIN_NODE_BINARY`. Touched in 45c5a7118 alongside the parallel `mk-code-graph.js` changes covered in the system-code-graph v1.1.0.0 release. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.3.0.md:61:This release is backward-compatible for every existing user. Operators who passed configuration via `rawOptions` only continue to work, `rawOptions` still wins at the top of the precedence chain. Operators who used environment variables only continue to work, the legacy `SPEC_KIT_PLUGIN_NODE_BINARY` fallback is preserved and the new `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_*` variables are additive. Operators who used neither continue to work, the hardcoded defaults are unchanged from v0.2.0. The metrics file format on disk is unchanged. Existing files are read and rewritten through the new awaited code path without schema changes. Source commits: 65e6f0479, 45c5a7118.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:3:This first preview release establishes `system-skill-advisor` as a standalone MCP server that owns prompt-time skill recommendation. The package was extracted from `system-spec-kit`, given a dedicated MCP identity (`mk_skill_advisor`), decoupled from spec-kit's source tree and wired into every install + diagnostic surface. The release covers eight public tools (`advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate`, `skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate`) reachable through the `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*` namespace. The 0.1 line keeps shadow-mode + parity gates in place while corpus and holdout metrics mature.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:7:- Need: advisor recommendation lived inside `system-spec-kit`, mixing skill graph and advisor scoring with spec-kit's memory and lifecycle code.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:8:- Change: the package now ships as `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/` with its own runtime, a dedicated `.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs` and a package-local SQLite database at `mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:16:- Change: the standalone server registers `advisor_recommend`, `advisor_rebuild`, `advisor_status` and `advisor_validate`. `advisor_recommend` returns prompt-safe `recommendations[]` plus cache + lifecycle metadata and `advisor_validate` returns real corpus, holdout, parity, safety and latency measurements.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:17:- Why it matters: every runtime can call the same MCP-native advisor surface with fail-open semantics, instead of forking subprocess shims per host.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:21:#### Skill graph, 4 graph tools
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:23:- Need: maintainers wanted to inspect, query and validate the skill graph directly without bouncing through advisor scoring.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:24:- Change: `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status` and `skill_graph_validate` expose the package-local SQLite graph. Lifecycle, freshness and trust state mirror the advisor tools.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:25:- Why it matters: skill-graph rebuilds, audits and integration checks have a stable MCP surface that other skills (and tests) can depend on.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:39:- Need: existing prompt hooks and CLI consumers depended on the Python `skill_advisor.py` shim and the OpenCode plugin bridge.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:40:- Change: `skill_advisor.py` probes the native advisor first and translates the response back to the legacy JSON-array shape. If the native probe is unavailable, it falls back to the local Python scorer. `--force-native` and `--force-local` testing toggles ship for rollback debugging. The OpenCode plugin bridge mirrors the same fail-open pattern.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:47:- Need: the skill had an `INSTALL_GUIDE.md`, but the master install README and `/doctor:mcp install` / `/doctor:mcp debug` enumerated four MCP servers without registering `mk_skill_advisor`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:48:- Change: added new §10.5 Skill Advisor subsection to the master install README and registered `mk_skill_advisor` in `mcp-doctor.sh` (new `diagnose_mk_skill_advisor()` function), `doctor_mcp_install.yaml`, `doctor_mcp_debug.yaml` and `mcp.md`. Inserted the previously-missing `mk_skill_advisor` block into `.vscode/mcp.json` for runtime parity across all six configs.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:67:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/INSTALL_GUIDE.md` | Added | Skill-level bootstrap guide following the sk-doc `skill_reference_install_guide` template. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:68:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md` | Added | Runtime routing instructions and invariants for `mk_skill_advisor`. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:69:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/README.md` | Added | Human-facing overview, advisor tools, skill-graph tools, FAQ. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:70:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/ARCHITECTURE.md` | Added | Subsystem boundaries, dependency direction, advisor + skill-graph topology. |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/changelog/v0.1.0.md:71:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py` | Added | Python compatibility shim with `--force-native` / `--force-local` toggles. |
