   123	
   124	---
   125	
   126	## 6. RUNTIME HOOKS AND PLUGIN
   127	
   128	Prompt-time routing is available across runtime adapters:
   129	
   130	| Runtime | Hook Surface |
   131	| --- | --- |
   132	| Claude Code | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/hooks/claude/user-prompt-submit.ts` |
   133	| Gemini CLI | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/hooks/gemini/user-prompt-submit.ts` |
   134	| Codex CLI | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.ts` plus `prompt-wrapper.ts` fallback and `lib/codex-hook-policy.ts` |
   135	| Devin CLI | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/hooks/devin/user-prompt-submit.ts` via `.devin/hooks.v1.json` |
   136	| OpenCode | `.opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js` plus the cross-process gateway at `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs` |
   137	
   138	The OpenCode bridge must use the stable package entrypoint:
   139	
   140	```text
   141	.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/compat/index.ts
   142	```
   143	
   144	After build, plugin consumers load:
   145	
   146	```text
   147	.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/dist/mcp_server/compat/index.js
   148	```
   149	
   150	---
   151	
   152	## 7. COMPAT SHIMS
   153	
   154	`skill_advisor.py` remains the CLI compatibility surface. In one-shot mode it probes the native advisor first and translates `advisor_recommend` output back to the legacy JSON-array shape. If the native probe is unavailable, it falls back to the local Python scorer.
   155	
   156	```bash
   157	python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py "help me commit my changes"
   158	printf '%s' "help me commit my changes" | python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --stdin
   159	```
   160	
   161	Mode meanings:
   162	
   163	| Mode | Behavior |
   164	| --- | --- |
   165	| default | Probe native. Use native if live/stale. Otherwise local Python fallback. |
   166	| `--stdin` | Read one prompt from stdin. |
   167	| `--force-native` | Require native routing and fail prompt-safely when unavailable. |
   168	| `--force-local` | Bypass native routing and run local Python scoring. |
   169	
   170	Testing controls:
   171	
   172	```bash
   173	python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --force-native "save this context"
   174	python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --force-local "save this context"
   175	```
   176	
   177	The OpenCode plugin bridge follows the same pattern: MCP-level `mk_skill_advisor.advisor_recommend` delegation with prompt-safe fail-open behavior. Plugin consumers must use the stable bridge entrypoint:
   178	
   179	```text
   180	.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs

