    36	- [`advisor_scorer.md`](./advisor_scorer.md)
    37	- [`tool_ids_reference.md`](../runtime/tool_ids_reference.md)
    38	
    39	---
    40	
    41	## 2. CURRENT BASELINES
    42	
    43	Baseline numbers as of remediation SHA `97a318d83`:
    44	
    45	| Metric | Baseline | Source |
    46	|---|---:|---|
    47	| Full-corpus top-1 accuracy | 80.5% | `mcp_server/tests/scorer/corpus.vitest.ts` |
    48	| Holdout top-1 accuracy | 77.5% | `mcp_server/tests/scorer/holdout.vitest.ts` |
    49	| UNKNOWN count (full corpus) | <= 10 | `advisor_validate` `telemetry.unknownCount` |
    50	| Python regression suite | full pass | `mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_regression.py` |
    51	| Advisor vitest tests | 167 across 23 files | `mcp_server/tests/` |
    52	| Watcher idle CPU | 0.031% | `mcp_server/lib/daemon/watcher.ts` benchmark |
    53	| Watcher idle RSS | 5.516 MB | same |
    54	| Cache-hit p95 latency | ~6.989 ms | `mcp_server/bench/cache-latency.bench.ts` |
    55	| Uncached p95 latency | ~11.45 ms | same |
    56	
    57	Drift threshold: top-1 accuracy below 80.5% on full corpus OR below 77.5% on holdout is a hard regression that blocks ship.
    58	
    59	---
    60	
    61	## 3. RUNNING VALIDATE
    62	
    63	`advisor_validate` is a heavy operation. It runs the full corpus plus holdout plus parity plus safety plus latency slices in one pass. Require `confirmHeavyRun=true` to invoke.
    64	
    65	```text
    66	mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate({ "confirmHeavyRun": true })
    67	```
    68	
    69	For a single-skill check (skip corpus + holdout):
    70	
    71	```text
    72	mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate({ "confirmHeavyRun": true, "skillSlug": "sk-code" })
    73	```
    74	
    75	Response fields to retain for baseline tracking:
    76	
    77	- `overallAccuracy` (float 0..1)
    78	- `slices.corpus.topOne` (float)
    79	- `slices.holdout.topOne` (float)
    80	- `slices.parity.passed` (boolean)
    81	- `slices.safety.violations` (integer count)
    82	- `slices.latency.cacheHitP95Ms` (float)
    83	- `telemetry.unknownCount` (integer)
    84	- `telemetry.lanesDominantCount` (object keyed by lane)
    85	- `perSkill[]` (array of per-skill results)
    86	- `generatedAt` (ISO timestamp)
    87	
    88	---
    89	
    90	## 4. INTERPRETING SLICES
    91	
    92	### Corpus slice
    93	
    94	Runs every skill in the full corpus through the scorer. Top-1 accuracy is the percent of prompts where the correct skill ranks first. Baseline 80.5%.
    95	
    96	Drift signal: a drop of more than 2 percentage points. Likely causes are scorer weight changes, new skills disrupting the lexical lane or stale skill metadata.
    97	
    98	### Holdout slice
    99	
   100	Runs a curated subset reserved for measuring generalization. Top-1 accuracy is the percent where the correct skill ranks first. Baseline 77.5%.
   101	
   102	Drift signal: drop > 1pp is a stronger regression signal than the corpus slice because holdout is unseen during weight tuning.
   103	
   104	### Parity slice
   105	
   106	Checks that the Python shim plus the native MCP scorer return the same recommendations for the same prompt. Pass means parity holds.
   107	
   108	Drift signal: any parity failure. Indicates a divergence between native plus Python paths. Inspect the failing prompt to identify which path drifted.
   109	
   110	### Safety slice

