    57	---
    58	
    59	## 4. OUTPUT CONTRACT
    60	
    61	The scorer emits JSON with:
    62	- `status`
    63	- `profileId`
    64	- `family`
    65	- `evaluationMode` (always `"dynamic-5d"`)
    66	- `target`
    67	- `candidate`
    68	- `score` (weighted dynamic score)
    69	- `dimensions` (array of 5 dimension objects)
    70	- `recommendation`
    71	- `failureModes`
    72	- `legacyScore` (always `null`; retained for schema compatibility)
    73	
    74	The benchmark runner emits JSON with:
    75	- `status`
    76	- `profileId`
    77	- `family`
    78	- `label`
    79	- `aggregateScore`
    80	- `maxScore`
    81	- `recommendation`
    82	- `fixtures`
    83	- `failureModes`
    84	
    85	### Dimension Details
    86	
    87	Each entry in the `dimensions` array contains `name`, `score`, `weight`, and `details`. The recommendation is `"candidate-acceptable"` when the weighted score is at least 70, otherwise `"needs-improvement"`.
    88	
    89	---
    90	
    91	## 5. RUBRIC
    92	
    93	### 5-Dimension Rubric (dynamic mode)
    94	
    95	| Dimension | Weight | What It Checks |
    96	| --- | --- | --- |
    97	| Structural Integrity | 0.20 | Agent template compliance (CORE WORKFLOW, OUTPUT VERIFICATION, ANTI-PATTERNS, CAPABILITY SCAN, RULES, RELATED RESOURCES sections) |
    98	| Rule Coherence | 0.25 | ALWAYS/NEVER/ESCALATE IF rules align with workflow steps and instructions; keyword match against the agent's own stated rules |
    99	| Integration Consistency | 0.25 | Runtime mirrors in sync, commands reference agent, skills reference agent; scored via `scan-integration.cjs` (mirror 60%, command 20%, skill 20%) |
   100	| Output Quality | 0.15 | Output verification checklist items present in instructions; no placeholder content ([TODO], [TBD], [YOUR_VALUE_HERE]) |
   101	| System Fitness | 0.15 | Permission-capability alignment (no tools listed but denied); resource references valid (commands and skills exist); frontmatter completeness (name, mode, permission) |
   102	
   103	### Benchmark Rubric
   104	
   105	| Dimension | Weight | What It Checks |
   106	| --- | --- | --- |
   107	| Structure | 0.45 | Required headings or sections appear in the output |
   108	| Grounding | 0.35 | Required file, command, or context references appear |
   109	| Cleanliness | 0.20 | Placeholders and forbidden patterns are absent |
   110	| Integration | optional | Mirror parity, command alignment, skill coverage (via `--integration-report`) |
   111	
   112	---
   113	
   114	## 6. REJECTION AND INFRA FAILURE
   115	
   116	Reject immediately when:
   117	- required target-profile sources are missing
   118	- the candidate omits the target's mandatory contract anchors
   119	- nested delegation is allowed where forbidden
   120	- placeholders dominate the body
   121	- the manifest marks the surface as forbidden or fixed
   122	- a benchmark run drops below the profile minimum fixture or aggregate score
   123	
   124	Use `infra_failure` only when the scorer or benchmark runner cannot read files, parse the manifest or profile, or load the fixture or output set.
   125	
   126	---
   127	
   128	## 7. RELATED RESOURCES
   129	
   130	- `benchmark_operator_guide.md`
   131	- `../shared/promotion_rules.md`
   132	- `../shared/promotion_rules.md`
   133	- `../scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs`
   134	- `../scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs`
   135	- `../scripts/agent-improvement/generate-profile.cjs`
     1	---
     2	title: Benchmark Operator Guide
     3	description: Step-by-step guide for running repeatable fixture benchmarks for deep-agent-improvement target profiles.
     4	---
     5	
     6	# Benchmark Operator Guide
     7	
     8	Operational guide for running deep-agent-improvement benchmarks against packet-local outputs. Use it when you need deterministic evidence that a target profile still behaves consistently across repeated runs.
     9	
    10	---
    11	
    12	## 1. OVERVIEW
    13	
    14	### Purpose
    15	
    16	Explains how to run deterministic fixture benchmarks, where to store the resulting evidence, and how to interpret repeatability.
    17	
    18	### When to Use
    19	
    20	Use this reference when:
    21	- Running the benchmark runner for any dynamic-mode target
    22	- Building repeatability evidence for a promotion gate
    23	- Checking whether a target profile is stable enough to trust
    24	
    25	### Core Principle
    26	
    27	Benchmark truth is output-based. The runner judges produced packet-local artifacts, not just how a prompt file reads.
    28	
    29	The copied runtime templates use the `improvement_*` asset names, but the packet-local runtime files produced by the current workflow use the `agent-improvement-*` naming family.
    30	
    31	---
    32	
    33	## 2. RUNNER COMMAND
    34	
    35	```text
    36	node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs \
    37	  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \
    38	  --outputs-dir {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs
    39	
    40	node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs \
    41	  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \
    42	  --outputs-dir {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs
    43	```
    44	
    45	### Scorer Selection
    46	
    47	`run-benchmark.cjs` defaults to `--scorer pattern` (the byte-identical heading and pattern matcher). Add `--scorer 5dim` to route the materialized outputs through the five-dimension scorer (`scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs`), and `--grader noop|mock|llm` to pick the D4 grader (default `noop`, deterministic). The report and `benchmark_run` record carry `scoringMethod: pattern` or `scoringMethod: 5dim`.
    48	
    49	```text
    50	node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs \
    51	  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \
    52	  --outputs-dir {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs \
    53	  --scorer 5dim --grader noop
    54	```
    55	
    56	### Integration Benchmark
    57	
    58	When running with an integration report, add the `--integration-report` flag:
    59	
    60	```text
    61	node scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs --profile .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json --outputs-dir=... --integration-report=integration-report.json
    62	```
    63	
    64	The integration report adds `integrationScore` and `integrationDetails` to the benchmark output:
    65	- `mirrorScore` (0-100): deducts 30 per missing mirror, 20 per diverged mirror
    66	- `commandScore` (0/100): at least 1 command references the agent
    67	- `skillScore` (0/100): at least 1 skill references the agent
    68	- Weighted: 60% mirror + 20% command + 20% skill
    69	
    70	---
    71	
    72	## 3. REQUIRED LAYOUT
    73	
    74	```text
    75	{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs/
    76	  fixture-baseline.md
    77	  fixture-improved.md
    78	  fixture-edge.md
    79	  report.json
    80	```
    81	
    82	---
    83	
    84	## 4. REPEATABILITY RULE
    85	
    86	- Run the same fixture or output set at least twice
    87	- Scores must remain identical when inputs are identical
    88	- If scores drift, stop and treat the harness as unstable
    89	
    90	---
    91	
    92	## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA
    93	
    94	Benchmark success means:
    95	- aggregate score meets the profile threshold
    96	- no fixture falls below the profile minimum fixture score
    97	- forbidden placeholder or fabrication patterns do not appear
    98	- the benchmark record is appended to the packet-local ledger
    99	
   100	Benchmark success does not mean:
   101	- a mirror sync passed downstream checks
   102	- a prompt-surface score exists with no benchmark evidence
   103	- a benchmark run passed only once
   104	
   105	---
   106	
   107	## 6. RELATED RESOURCES
   108	
   109	- `evaluator_contract.md`
   110	- `../shared/loop_protocol.md`
   111	- `../shared/promotion_rules.md`

